  9  # Basic properties of holors
 10  
 11  Holors are indexed collections of tensor coefficients. Confusingly,
 12  they are often called tensors in physics and in the neural network
 13  community.
 14  
 15  A holor is simply a multidimensional array of values. The size of a
 16  holor is specified by a `list ℕ`, whose length is called the dimension
 17  of the holor.
 18  
 19  The tensor product of `x₁ : holor α ds₁` and `x₂ : holor α ds₂` is the
 20  holor given by `(x₁ ⊗ x₂) (i₁ ++ i₂) = x₁ i₁ * x₂ i₂`. A holor is "of
 21  rank at most 1" if it is a tensor product of one-dimensional holors.
 22  The CP rank of a holor `x` is the smallest N such that `x` is the sum
 23  of N holors of rank at most 1.
 24  
 25  Based on the tensor library found in <https://www.isa-afp.org/entries/Deep_Learning.html>
 26  
 27  ## References
 28  
 29  * <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tensor_rank_decomposition>
